The paper discusses a reinforcement learning algorithm that combines a distributional perspective with a distributed framework for off-policy learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The algorithm is applied to continuous control tasks, which suggests that robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions locomotion tasks, which suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) may also be a relevant sub-category.
